Building asciidoc presentation:
- download and install asciidoc (with slidy) and graphviz
- from on of the presentations folder run:
	./makeslides
- For example in the presentations/git-gerrit/workshop/ folder

Output for presentations:
- The current actively used master file is: git-workshop.txt 
- creates git-workshop.html

Open a presentation:
- open the resulting *.html document in a web browser
- use the same keys like in PowerPoint to move forward and back

Building exercises:
- from exercise folder run:
    make html
  or
    make pdf
